Sex Diaries: Webcam Couples
Film-maker Charlie Russell interviews four of the growing number of ordinary couples who choose to broadcast their sex lives on the internet. Midlanders Moses and Kitty - as they like to call themselves - have made a full-time job out of titillating strangers, whereas another couple just do it for kicks. The film explores what drives them to share their sexual adventures online, and discovers what effect giving up their privacy in the bedroom has on their lives, their families and their relationships. Glenn and Ari are newlyweds who even webcammed on their honeymoon and don't charge viewers to watch them, while Emma and Eddie claim to make a six-figure salary. Kitty and Moses webcam as a way of making extra cash, performing one-on-one sex shows between cups of tea from the comfort of their own front room.
